As exclusive agents, CBRE are pleased to announce that 79-81 Liverpool Road, Burwood is for sale via Public Auction.

This represents an exciting opportunity to acquire one of the last land holdings on Liverpool road with a development upside in the heart of one of the most sought after suburbs within the Inner West.

Additional highlights outlined below:

-Land area: 1,180sqm*
-B2- Local Centre/FSR 1.5:1
-Holding Income
-Allowing multiple uses: Residential development, Service stations, Boarding house, Child care, Commercial premises (STCA)
-Extraordinary location in close proximity to transport infrastructure
-1.3km* to Burwood train station
-1.9km* to Burwood Westfield's
-7km* to Concord Hospital or Sydney Olympic Park
-2km* to Parramatta Road with direct route 12km* to Sydney CBD

Site Dimensions:
Frontage: 20m*
Length: 59m*

For an information memorandum or further details please contact the Exclusive Agents listed.

*approx.

CBRE as the exclusive agency is pleased to present 40-46 Stanley Street, Burwood. Currently four single storey houses in-one-line, the property is a DA approved development site for a boarding house including a total of 95 rooms. In addition to the approved boarding house, the R1 General Residential zoning also permits (with consent) alternative development options including Multi Dwelling Housing, Residential Flat Building, Serviced Apartments, Childcare Centre and Shop Top Housing etc. The development yield for an apartment scheme is circa 38 to 42 apartments (STCA). Conveniently located close to the heart of Burwood, the suburb boasts some of Sydney’s best Asian cuisine and a great mix of amenities and restaurants along the thriving main retail strip on Burwood Road; the rapidly growing suburb is centred around Burwood Westfield and Burwood train station.

The property benefits from the following key attributes:
•	DA approved for a boarding house including a total of 95 rooms
•	Large combined site area of 1,567sqm*
•	Flexible zoning with alternative development options (STCA)
•	R1 General Residential zoning with 14m height limit
•	Favourable location close to array of restaurants, amenities, Burwood Station & Westfield Burwood
•	2,611sqm* of DA approved GFA

40-46 Stanley Street, Burwood will be sold via Expressions of interest closing on Wednesday 18th November 2020 at 4pm

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

CBRE as exclusive agents are pleased to offer 17 Deane Street, Burwood for sale by way of EOI, closing on 2nd December 2015 at 3pm.

 Key attributes of the property are:

 - B4 mixed Use, 6:1 FSR & 70m Height
 - Site Area of 1,084sqm*
 - 3 street frontages
 - Opposite Burwood Train Station
 - 300m to Westfield Shopping Centre & Burwood Plaza
 - Unique land holding in Burwood CBD

For more information please contact the listed agents.
